author: Sarah
text: My friend and I signed up at this gym a few months back with their opening offer and we always have a good experience here. During the week we often visit other Anytime outlets due to our hectic schedule but this Macpherson mall outlet is our favourite and we try to visit at least twice a week. Justin and all the staff members are helpful and friendly. This outlet is well-maintained in terms of facilities and cleanliness too. Hope they continue to manage the upkeep well.

author: Ney Rinda
text:
I‚Äôve been working out at Anytime Fitness MacPherson Mall and it‚Äôs been a fantastic experience! The gym is clean, well-maintained, and never too crowded, making it a comfortable space to train anytime, day or night.

The equipment is in excellent condition with a good variety for both cardio and strength training. What really sets this branch apart is the team ‚Äî the staff and trainers are friendly, approachable, and always ready to help. Whether you‚Äôre a beginner or a regular gym-goer, the positive atmosphere here makes it easy to stay motivated.

Our group of friends enjoys coming here regularly, and we always have a great time working out together. A special mention to Linda ‚Äì she is very kind, approachable, and always ready to help whenever we need assistance. Highly recommend this gym!

text: an amazing gym with a clean and super well-maintained space. they have all the equipment you could ever need! their staff (kirtan and linda!) are extremely friendly and always ready to help! and i love that has plenty of parking and is very accessible. the atmosphere is welcoming and the place is never too crowded, even during peak hours. i have put off my fitness for the longest time, i hope here is where that all changes. i highly recommend anytime fitness macpherson mall!

text: The gym was very well equipped with many new machines and free weights. Everything was new and the staff was friendly. Had a session with PT Kirtan and he really helped me understand more about lifting with the proper forms and the science behind every movements while being pain free! Highly recommend anyone from a beginner to professionals to have a session with him!

Those who want to try muay thai training with Trainer Ehsaan, you can definitely make your trip here. üôè

author: Johnnywoosh
text:
Solid gym. Sign up a breeze with the female gym staff( I assume is Linda?) and we could workout the same day.
(If you have a old dongle, bring it along)

Equipment brand new. Accessories in great condition. A lot of cables to accommodate a big crowd. 2 lat pull downs.

Many squat racks and 2 platforms in a separate unit. Back extension, hack squat, glute, low row plate loaded machines VERY well made. Kudos management for bringing them in, seriously.

Smells good, very clean. Happy to sign here. Please keep it up!

Little suggestion:
Perhaps add a weight horn by the plate loaded machines as it gets hard to access the big plates with 2.5/5s in the way.

author: Danielle Tay
text:
Always a positive experience here. The gym is always clean, the staff are welcoming, and I appreciate the 24-hour access. Highly recommend!

I had my introductory one-on-one training session with Kirtan and it was an absolutely fantastic experience. His knowledge and attention to detail are truly impressive. He didn't just walk me through exercises; he meticulously analyzed my posture and helped me understand exactly what I was doing wrong. Thanks to his guidance, I now know how to properly engage the correct muscles, which will make a huge difference in my workouts.

author: Pamela Chan
text: Having a wonderful experience with Ehsaan, he is a great trainer and knows the human biology very well (explains in simple ways for me to understand on how to be healthier, build muscle and lose fat through science). Will recommend for anyone to start training with him especially females who wants to look athletic and toned

author: Aaron Kueh
text:
As someone who started with zero knowledge about fitness or how to begin a weight loss journey, finding the right trainer made all the difference.

If you‚Äôre looking for a trainer who‚Äôs approachable, encouraging, and really understands how to tailor workouts to your individual needs, I highly recommend Nico. He‚Äôs not only great at what he does, but he genuinely cares about your progress.

Having Nico as my trainer has helped me stay consistent and motivated. He keeps track of my progress, adjusts the workouts as needed, and makes the whole process a lot less intimidating. Whether you‚Äôre just starting out or looking to get back on track, Nico‚Äôs support can make a big difference.

author: Meena Asohan
text:
Anytime Fitness Mcpherson Mall has a welcoming atmosphere for people of all fitness levels. The equipment is modern and new, providing a large variety of options for exercise.

I took the starter pack for personal training as I've never worked out in a gym setting before. My trainer, Kirtan, was highly knowledgeable and motivating, creating a personalized workout plan that suited my fitness level.  He provided support and encouragement which helped me get confident and familiar in the gym environment.

I highly recommend this gym and its trainers for anyone seeking to improve their health and achieve their fitness goals!

author: Joy
text: Anytime Fitness MacPherson is impressive. Clean, spacious, and rarely crowded. 24/7 access is a big plus. Limited showers since it relies on mall facilities, but overall a top choice for effective, no-frills training. Linda was friendly and helpful!

author: C Loh
text:
I had the joy of attending the launch of this new gym last Saturday, and I‚Äôm still buzzing from the energy. Tucked away in the basement of a rather unassuming building, this space has been completely transformed into a space that radiates warmth, grit, and genuine community spirit.

What struck me most wasn‚Äôt just the equipment or the space (though both are great), but the people. From the moment I stepped in, I was welcomed with open arms by the trainers, the members, even folks I‚Äôd never met before. It already feels like a second home for those who come here, and it‚Äôs only just opened.

Huge kudos to HM for bringing this vision to life, for creating not just a gym, but a safe, supportive, and motivating environment for people to move, sweat, and grow stronger together. So proud and excited to see where this journey leads!

author: Min Hui Tan
text: Very large and better equipped compared to most AF gyms, with solid, top-end equipment. Friendly staff and I‚Äôm a regular training with Kirtan- super experienced, yet friendly and utterly grounded. Highly recommended!

author: St Yiling
text:
Highly recommend this Anytime Fitness branch! üí™

The gym is super comfortable, clean, and has everything you need. But the real stars here are the hilarious and awesome trainers ‚Äî Nico and Kirtan! Every session with them is not only effective, but also full of laughs. They‚Äôll make sure you‚Äôre doing the exercises the proper way (even if it means correcting your squat for the 10th time üòÖ).

If you want to get fit, learn the right techniques, and have a good time doing it ‚Äî this is the place to be!

author: Hwee Chong Chua
text: Very new and clean gym at Macpherson Mall. The showers, changing rooms, and lockers make workouts fuss-free. Equipment is modern, comprehensive and well taken care of. The crowd there are friendly, welcoming and the overall vibe of the place is great!

author: Chi Hong Hwang
text:
I have been training under Kirtan for about 2 to 3 years. He is great. He has deep knowledge about functional training and helped me through chronic pain in both my shoulders. He still continues to go for more training and certification and works the new knowledge into my weekly training. Now that we've moved to this gym, I'm pleased that he has incorporated heavier weights into my workout. I always enjoy my sessions with Kirtan. He's easy going and easy to talk to. Over the years we've become friends.

They gym is newly renovated so it is clean, well lit and well equipped. There's a good buzz. I was surprised at the many bodybuilder enthusiasts there on a weekday evening but still there was little wait for machines. The gym was located in the basement. A door in the car park opens to the gym entrance after a shot passage. So park at the correct side of the car park.

The mall itself is undergoing a revitalisation. Parts of it  was still somewhat worn and old but then it makes you appreciate all the more how bright, new and shiny the gym is.

author: Timon Tai
text:
I've been training with Kirtan for over two years now, and I can honestly say he‚Äôs one of the best personal trainers out there. What sets him apart is his deep, holistic understanding of body mechanics. Unlike the typical brute-force, muscle-building approach you get with many trainers, Kirtan focuses on integrating movement, balance, and mobility in a way that makes your body feel stronger and better after every session.

No two workouts are ever the same ‚Äî I haven‚Äôt repeated a single set in all this time. Every lesson is thoughtfully planned, challenging, and fun. And if you ever feel like mixing it up, he also incorporates boxing, which adds another layer of excitement and intensity.

I‚Äôve seen real results, but more importantly, I feel better in my body ‚Äî more aware, more agile, and more resilient. Highly recommend Kirtan to anyone looking for training that‚Äôs intelligent, engaging, and truly transformative.

author: Keerthana Ravichandran
text:
BoxCore Fitness class was the best! all thanks to our incredible Trainer Kirtan! From the very beginning, the energy was high and the atmosphere was welcoming.

We kicked things off with a fun and energising warm-up that really set the tone. Kirtan expertly taught us key boxing techniques like the forward punch, slip, uppercut, and hook. Each move was broken down with clear explanations, and Kirtan patiently guided us through every step, making sure we got the form and rhythm right.

What truly stood out was how well-versed and passionate Kirtan is in boxing, his experience shines through in every instruction and correction. Whether you're brand new or just brushing up your skills, you'll learn so much!

We wrapped up with a cool down and stretching session that was not only effective but also really enjoyable, a perfect way to end an intense workout. Overall, it was an fun experience.

author: Huiling Lee
text:
Finally moved with Kirtan my Personal Trainer from December 2022 to a new cleaner and better equipped Gym in Anytime Fitness MacPherson Mall.
The gym has super Precor machines and adequate weights. The lighting is great and it smells lovely ‚Ä¶lemongrass and newness.  Hope they keep up the cleanliness!!! Most importantly, Kirtan my PT is wonderful‚Ä¶patiently working with me‚Ä¶. Post super sedentary lifestyle, sarcopaenic, flat-footed and imbalanced. We have worked through post cardiac surgery, fractured ankle and now I am mostly pain free and working towards building muscle, strength and functionality.  Am now at my ideal body weight and soon I will be able to achieve some bucket lists items like wall climbing ‚Ä¶. So but steadily, Kirtan has been backing me, instructing and correcting all the functional postural and strength issues. Thanks for the hard work and patience.
